initialization during the JVM agent phase for dynamic access coverage. Maybe I should inspect the build reports and test logs. There's also the possibility that an added file isn't tracked. I might consider creating a test that loads ApacheCatalogResolver with a URLClassLoader.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating dynamic tracking and class loading**\\n\\nI’m realizing that the dynamic tracker likely instruments library classes loaded from the regular dependency. If I'm using a custom loader with the same JAR, that should also get instrumented, right? I'm thinking the duplicate in AntClassLoader might not be initialized because `forceLoadClass` didn't trigger it. I need to verify that AntClassLoader's `initializeClass` works correctly with the right arguments. To move forward, I'd better initialize the actual constructor using `resolverClass.newInstance()`. This feels like a good reflection strategy for testing dynamic loading via AntClassLoader.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering reflection handling**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether the parent should be included for the xml-resolver. It seems it might not be necessary. I wonder if I need to handle the Class#newInstance reflection call within the test itself, maybe to ensure I add coverage? But I'm not targeting it specifically. Also, can I catch ReflectiveOperationException? The method throws generic Exception, which adds some uncertainty.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_wj0CShSym8dWY9iD4YHhW7dz|fc_0aa938860c6eeb2d0169f5917e7e648193b199b37779dc59b5", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/src/test/java/ant/ant/ApacheCatalogResolverTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "    private static final String PUBLIC_ID = \"-//Example//DTD Apache Resolver Entry//EN\";\n    private static final String URI = \"http://example.test/apache-resolver-entry.xml\";\n", "newText": "    private static final String RESOLVER_CLASS_NAME =\n            \"org.apache.tools.ant.types.resolver.ApacheCatalogResolver\";\n    private static final String PUBLIC_ID = \"-//Example//DTD Apache Resolver Entry//EN\";\n    private static final String URI = \"http://example.test/apache-resolver-entry.xml\";\n"}, {"oldText": "            Class<?> resolverClass = classLoader.forceLoadClass(\n                    ApacheCatalogResolver.class.getName());\n            assertThat(resolverClass.getClassLoader()).isSameAs(classLoader);\n            AntClassLoader.initializeClass(resolverClass);\n\n            assertThat(System.getProperty(\"xml.catalog.className\"))\n                    .isEqualTo(ApacheCatalog.class.getName());\n", "newText": "            Class<?> resolverClass = classLoader.forceLoadClass(RESOLVER_CLASS_NAME);\n            assertThat(resolverClass.getClassLoader()).isSameAs(classLoader);\n\n            Object resolver = resolverClass.newInstance();\n\n            assertThat(resolverClass.getName()).isEqualTo(RESOLVER_CLASS_NAME);\n            assertThat(resolver).isNotNull();\n            assertThat(System.getProperty(\"xml.catalog.className\"))\n                    .isEqualTo(ApacheCatalog.class.getName());\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3013, "output": 1880, "cacheRead": 43520, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 48413, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777701221573, "responseId": "resp_0aa938860c6eeb2d0169f5916622d08193a9c8acbba1f651f2"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_wj0CShSym8dWY9iD4YHhW7dz|fc_0aa938860c6eeb2d0169f5917e7e648193b199b37779dc59b5", "toolName": "edit", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully replaced 2 block(s) in tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/src/test/java/ant/ant/ApacheCatalogResolverTest.java."}], "details": {"diff": "     ...\n  25 \n  26 import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n  27 \n  28 public class ApacheCatalogResolverTes